HRR.title: विस्मृति !!
HRR.about:
Everything good must come to an end. The worst thing about being a fan of nightcore or any genre of music is that when you die, you can no longer listen to it. Not many religions mention nightcore in their holy texts or oral traditions, but we're doubtless that many a nightcore fan is spiritual. These pieces were created in order to attenuate noise during seances, allowing one to come closer with the spirit realm.
The recordings themselves have only been shared on tape among in-the-know nightcore fans, but we've received permission from a certain archivist to release them to the general public. These recordings are considered sacred, and should be listened to with the the utmost care. However, we've also chosen to include a club friendly remix commissioned from veteran post-nightcore musician, Fuuka ASMR. We hope this trip into nightcore esotericism doesn't lead you down a dangerous path as the recordings themselves are associated with at least 9 deaths.

HRR.title: Crushing Union V
HRR.about:
The Headspace duo Tatiana and Laura C. return with their 5th LP as the Crushing Union. The duo have dubbed their slow abrasive drone style as "dirge" music.
"Dirge is a sound I came up with to describe what we were doing with the Crushing Union releases. We'd make these original compositions and slow them down until they were these brutal artifacted industrial beats, the more slow and extreme a track is the more dirge it is." Says Laura C. who is definitely a real person.
While Crushing Union V is a softer dirge release (Calculated at being only 56% dirge), the duo hope it serves a pleasant example of the style.

HRR.title: NXCXTC EP
HRR.about:
After a protracted legal battle, Frederika Felicia Montero "Fuuka ASMR" Fasmr has regained the rights to NXCXTC from the Tennessee Nightcore Producer's Union. It was a long battle that cost both Fuuka ASMR and HRR management over $78 million dollar in legal fees and damages. We're all pretty traumatized after the long court process, especially since the court caught fire several times due to reasons unrelated to the trial. But we're fine, we're dry now, and we're in a warm place where intellectual property laws can't find us.
Enjoy NXCXTC EP, now freely available in the first of many coming re-releases and featuring the rare track, Senki Rave.
HRRE01

HRR.about:
B.G.S. means "Beans Gravy and Syrup" and is a side project of Tiana. She brings us "Pointless Living", a 4D percussive piece for the - now closed - clubs offered at a reasonable price. We're giving it you, it's not optional. It is Tiana's first gift of the year, and may it bring you to a modular truth.
HRR38

HRR.title: Poyo Mix
HRR.about:
Nightcore duo, DJ Poyo POYO, are known for creating several high profile nightcore mixes that hit airwaves in Lisbon back in 2009. Poyo Mix is their first mix that is readily available for consumption by the Western world. In their own words, Poyo Mix is best described as the "awkward in-betweens" of nightcore.
Taking influence from first wave nightcore, vaporwave, and even the stylings of Karlheinz Stockhausen, Poyo Mix is DJ Poyo POYO's first official step into a style of nightcore they've dubbed "Aniwave".

HRR.title: Reflective ASMR
HRR.about:
Hit producer, Fuuka ASMR, has returned from her semi-hiatus with a new introspective EP, Reflective ASMR. Billed as reflections on her life all but falling apart after the release of her smash hit pop nightcore EP, NXCXTC, Fuuka ASMR takes a complete 180 in both the meaning and sound of her music while still totally being nightcore. You definitely can't play these at a club, but sometimes it's just nice to sit back and listen to things by yourself or with close friends and business associates.

HRR.title: Soultek
HRR.about:
Yakui returns to HRR, this time with hardcore reflections on the isolation and ennui of rural Western Pennsylvanian life. Currently based out of the server room of an abandoned office building located in Cambria County, Yakui has molded a fusionist hardcore sound strictly grounded in the culture and land of modern rural Pennsylvanian youth. Dubbed "Soultek" this high-energy release is meant to raise the spirits of the listener, both figuratively and literally. The presence of anomalous binaural beats which resonate with the souls of [EXPUNGED] have lead to this albums preemptive banning in the countries of [EXPUNGED], [EXPUNGED], and [REDACTED]. We take no responsibility for incidences of mania or extreme violence that may occur from the playing of this album. Remember, HRR loves you.
HRR23

HRR.title: speedlove\\
HRR.about:
Recorded in the Balkan mountains and sent to us in a suspicious, unlabeled package, speedlove\\ is the debut EP from nightcore heavyweight, //buttercups. Apparently haunted and cursed, speedlove\\ has passed through the hands of many a nightcore DJ. Nobody who has come into possession of this EP has lived, but we here at Horrible Recordings are hoping to defy the unfathomable laws of the cosmos with this release.
An eclectic mix of both experimental and traditional nightcoring techniques, speedlove\\ is enough to make both hardcore nightcore fans and newcomers go wild. That's both figurative and literal.
soundcloud.com/fatherfake
HRR05

HRR.title: Squishy Moments
HRR.about:
Fuuka ASMR is a controversial figure in the nightcore scene. Known for her unorthodox take on nightcore, many nightcore purists don't consider her a nightcore artist at all. However, whatever your opinion on Fuuka ASMR may be, her approach towards production is philosophically to that of nightcore's forebearers.
Squishy Moments is a collection of long sought after Fuuka ASMR tracks. Usually placed at the end of nightcore mixes as "set closers", the Squishy Moments collection have remained exclusive only to top nightcore DJs until now.

HRR.title: Terri Howards EP
HRR.about:
8 year old Terri Howards has been making tsunamis in the nightcore scene with her futuristic bass boosted, nightcore tracks. Though it was originally designed to accompany Animal Crossing "let's plays", Terri's music has found a place on the walkmen of nightcore fans across the globe. Terri herself believes that the best way to enjoy her music is to do so while watching someone play Animal Crossing.

HRR.title: Untitled EP
HRR.about:
DJ Witchy Dreams is the alias of a producer and long time friend of the label who prefers to stay anonymous. For a short period of time in the early 2010s he created these tracks in hopes of becoming a gabber DJ. These tracks were shared anonymously on a number of sites dedicated to music and nerdy culture, but never caught on.
His dreams of being a famous gabber DJ never came true however, and he now has moved on to working in the much more respectable genre of hyperpop. Still, Mr. Witchy Dreams wished with all his heart that this EP could be released even if no one knew he made it. We (Tiana) at HRR had to oblige and bring these cutesy tracks to the public eye.
